Commentary: A back of a length ball, angling in, around off, defended to the off side by Butt.
On a length, sliding down the leg side, Butt looks to flick, but the ball takes the pad and the keeper dives to his left and takes it. An appeal but turned down. No bat there.
First runs of the Test! Butt and Pakistan get underway here. On a fuller length, outside off, Butt strokes this through covers and picks up a couple.
Good length around off, pushed to the point fielder.
Length ball outside off, Butt looks to have a feel of this but misses.
A dot to end the over! On a length in the fourth stump channel, Butt defends inside the line and misses. 2 from the opening over!
Jayden Seales starts with a short ball, outside the off pole, there is some bounce on this as Abid Ali makes a leave.
Length delivery, outside off, it shapes away as Ali makes a leave.
Length again, on off, blocked.

EDGED AND FOUR. Some element of luck for Ali and he gets off the mark. A hint of away movement on this one. Pitches it up, around off, the seams away as Ali looks to drive. Takes the outside edge and goes past the leaping gully fielder, to the ropes.
Short, outside off, left alone.
Full ball outside off, Abid Ali shoulders arms to it.
On off, blocked out.
Full ball on off, Imran Butt pushes it to mid off.
Full on middle and leg, Butt flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Full on middle, Butt pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Butt pushes it to cover for a single.
FOUR! That's a great looking shot. On a good length, on off and middle, this is gently pushed through mid on and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Outside off, left alone this time.
Length around off, shapes away, blocked out.
An awayswinger outside off, Butt shoulders arms this time.
Way wider outside off, Butt looks to drive this one but fails to make contact.
On a good length this time, outside off, Imran strokes this one through covers and picks up a brace.
Outside off, nipping away too, Butt watches it go past him to the keeper.
Full ball around off, Ali defends.
Short of a length ball this time, around off, coming in, Abid blocks it out.
Pushed to the mid off fielder on this occasion.
Abid makes another leave as this was bowled outside the off pole.
An action replay of the previous delivery.

Ouch! That would have stung. A back of a length ball, around off this time, nipping back in, the bounce gets too big on Ali as he looks to fend this to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the glove.
In the fourth stump channel, on a good length, Butt looks to have a poke but gets beaten.
Outside off this time, no shot offered.
Serves a short ball, outside the off pole, Butt leaves it.
Another length ball outside off, Imran leaves it be.
The batsman is not interested in playing at that. No ball called as Jayden Seales had overstepped.
FOUR! Jayden Seales looked to get too straight on this occasion and serves this one the pads, Butt flicks this one nicely to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Way outside off, on a shortish length, Butt leaves it.
Around off, defended out.
Good length ball on off, Abid looks to defend but it goes off the inner half to the leg side for one.
Outside off, nothing doing says Butt, as he leaves.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! Roach strikes early and Pakistan lose an early wicket. Excellent delivery from Kemar and Imran Butt goes back for a tame score. Kemar Roach hurls across a length delivery, around the off pole, Imran Butt looks to play too hard at this, as he looks to drive, but the ball nips in sharply this time. Takes the inside edge and crashes into the wickets behind. The hosts draw first blood!
Howout: b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Yorker at the base of off and middle, Azhar does well to defend.
Back of a length, around off, Azhar defends. A successful over from Roach!
Length around off, dabbed to the gully fielder.
Bangs in a short ball, outside off, Ali looks to slash this one away but misses.
Back of a length, outside off, Ali bunts this one to the off side.
In the fourth stump channel, outside off, the ball hits the deck and shapes away, Abid shoulders arms.
A carbon copy of the previous ball.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! That's a brilliant delivery from Seales and both the openers are sent packing for a low score. Jayden Seales bowls a length delivery, in the zone of uncertainty outside the off pole. The ball hits the deck and shapes away beautifully. Abid Ali is drawn forward, as he looks to block, but the away movement ensures that the edge is taken. Joshua Da Silva makes no mistakes behind the sticks. They check if this is a legal delivery and replays show that it was close, but some part of the boot, was behind the line. Two down inside the first hour, for the visitors!
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Around off, pushed to point for a single.
On off, nudged to the leg side.
Good length on off, defended to mid on.
FOUR! Babar gets off the mark in such a fine manner. Kemar Roach overpitches this outside off, Babar Azam leans into the shot and creams it through mid off for a boundary.
Length on off, blocked.
Outside off, on a length, Azam looks to defend but gets beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
Wider outside off, but still on a length, Azhar is happy to leave this one.
Back of a length, outside off, swinging away, Ali defends.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length outside off, Azhar is again calm as he leaves.
Left alone again by Azhar as it was bowled outside the off pole.
An outswinger in the fourth stump channel, no reason for Babar to play at this and so, he leaves.
Fuller, slower in pace, outside off, Azam does no offer a stroke.
Length ball, swinging away late. Babar Azam shoulders arms to it.
Azam is in no hurry to score runs as he makes another leave.
This time, since it is bowled on a length, closer to off, Azam pushes it to mid off.
Maiden from Mayers! Around off, on a length, pushed to covers.
Starts with a length ball down the leg side, Ali just leaves it.
Serves it on a length, nipping away, around off, Ali looks to dab it down, but the ball takes the edge and goes on the bounce to the slip cordon.
Outside off, good carry to the keeper as AA watches it go past him.
On a length, outside off, Ali looks to fend at this but gets beaten by the away movement.
The batsman is not interested in playing at that.
Ends the over with a good length delivery on middle, this is clipped through mid-wicket and the batters pick up a couple.
Shorter outside off, cut away past point for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Length around off, defended out.
Outside off on a length, Ali looks to have a poke at this but gets beaten.

A back of a length delivery, around off, nibbles back in and hits Ali high on the pad as he looks to flick. An appeal but turned down. There is a quick discussion but they do not go for the review. Too high, it looked like.
Outside off on a length, no shot offered this time.
Length on off, kept out this time.
Bowls this on a length, but down the leg side, Azam looks to flick but misses.
Quick single! A back of a length ball, on off, tapped to the off side for a single.
On a length, outside the off pole again, left alone by Azhar.
Short of a length, on off, Azhar defends it out.
On a fuller length, outside off, Azhar Ali again shows no interest to play at this.
On a length, outside off, Azam shoulders arms.
Mayers bowls an inswinger, fuller on off, Azam flicks this one through mid-wicket. They run hard and come back for the second run, by the time the ball can be returned into the middle.
On a fuller length, on off, AA strides forward and blocks well.
Fuller on off, Ali pushes this to covers.
On a fuller length, outside off, Azhar watches this one closely, but makes a leave in the end.
Well fielded by the short cover fielder there. On a fuller length, outside off, Ali stokes this towards covers, where Jomel Warrican dives to his left and stops the ball well.
A length ball, around off, Babar Azam rises with the bounce and fends it towards gully.
On a length, wide outside off, left alone.
Length ball, on off. Azam defends it to cover. There is a bit of a yes-no situation for the single but eventually, it is not taken.
Fuller, outside off, solidly blocked towards cover.
Slanting in with the angle outside off, Babar lets it through on bounce.
Around middle and leg, the skipper tucks it through square leg for one.
Fuller, outside off, Babar Azam drives it towards mid off.
Wide outside off, let through by Azam.
Full again, outside off, Babar drives it straight back to the bowler.
Around off, the skipper pushes it towards short cover.
Full, outside off, almot a yorker, Babar Azam digs it out to the off side.
On a good length, outside off, Azam shoulders arms.
Serves a good length ball on middle. Ali blocks it on the leg side.
Another good length ball outside off, shaping away. Left alone.

NOT OUT! Good review from Azhar Ali! A short of a length ball, outside off, it lands and straightens up. Azhar Ali looks to defend inside the line but seems to miss it. The keeper collects and appeals it immediately for caught behind. Ali reviews it and it shows that there is no bat involved. The on-field decision has been overturned.
On a length and on off. Ali defends it to covers.
Another length ball, around off. Ali blocks it on the off side.
A short of a length ball outside off. Ali shoulders arms to it.
Roach serves a length ball way outside off. Azam lets it through to the keeper.
Another length ball, way outside off. Azam leaves it alone to the keeper.
Serves a full ball, on middle, pushed to mid off.
Another length delivery which is way outside off. Left alone.
Wide outside off, on a length. Azam shoulders arms to it.
Good leave! On a length and outside off, nips back in. Azam watchfully leaves it to the keeper.
A back of a length ball on middle. Blocked out on the deck.
Touch fuller, way outside off, moving away. Ali lets it through.
Full again, outside off. Ali watchfully leaves it to the keeper.
On a length and on middle. Ali blocks it to mid off.

NOT OUT! Full again, on off. Ali punches it wide of mid off, down the ground to long off. The fielder chases back and fires in a throw to the bowler's end. Holder grabs it and removes the bails off. But the replay shows Ali was well in. Three taken in the end.
Around off, on a length. Azamlooks to defend but gets outer half of his bat to point.
A length ball, swinging in, outside off. Ali watchfully leaves it.
Another good length ball on middle. Ali defends it on the leg side.
This one holds its line. On a length and just around off. Azam looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Good delivery.
On middle, a fuller length, driven back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Another good length ball, outside off. Azam looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Roach needs to bowl in this line
FOUR! Ends the over with the boundary! A length ball outside off. Azam leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
A short of a length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Angles a length ball on middle, pushed to mid on.
Very full now, outside off. Ali shoulders arms to it.
Again full and outside off, moving away. Ali watchfully leaves it.
Touch fuller on middle. Ali solidly blocks it.

NOT OUT! Beauty of a delivery but Azhar Ali does not lose his wicket here! A good length ball, outside off, it lands and jags back in sharply. Ali shoulders arms to it but gets deceived by the movement and gets hit on the pad. The Windies appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Ali has a chat with his partner and goes for the review. It shows that the wickets were missing and Ali survives yet again. Another good review from Ali.
On a length and on off, pushed to covers.
Touch fuller and on off. Azam shows full face of the bat and pushes it through mid off for a single.
On middle, on a length, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full on middle, Defended.
Touch fuller on off. Ali defends it to the off side.
A good length ball outside off. Ali leaves it through.
Full on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
A short of a length ball on off. Ali hops and blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Ali taps it to the gully fielder.
Fuller ball, on off. Ali punches it to covers.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call saves Azhar Ali here! Holder angles in a full ball, around middle and leg. Ali strides forward and looks to defend under his eyes but gets hit on the pads. An appeal but the umpire says no. Holder was absolutely sure that it hit the pad first, and then bat. West Indies go for the review straightaway. Ultra edge confirms no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows it to be Umpire's Call on Impact, even though the ball was crashing into the wickets. Another reprieve for Ali.
On a length and on off. Blocked out.
A length ball way outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball on middle. Blocked out.
Full on the pads. Azam flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Another couple of runs! On a length and on middle. Azam clips it on the leg side and collects a brace.
A short of a length ball on middle. Azam punches it to covers.
FOUR! Fifty up for Pakistan! A length ball, outside off. Azam gets a thick outside edge, through the slip cordon, to the third man fence.
Goes full now, on middle. Ali flicks it to square leg for a couple of runs.
A length ball way outside off. Left alone.
Length ball on off. Ali punches it to covers and wanted a single but was sent back cleverly by Azam.
On a length and way outside off. Left alone.
Angles in a full ball on middle. Ali pushes it through covers for one.
Outside off, on a length, nips back in. Azam watchfully shoulders arms.
A wayward delivery, outside off. Ali lets it through to the keeper.
On a length, on off, moving in. Blocked out.
FOUR! Well played! A full ball way outside off. Ali, at the last moment knocks it through backward point for another boundary.
Another wide outside off delivery. Ali shoulders arms to it.

NOT OUT! Ali is like a cat, by the looks of things, seems like he has 9 lives. This is the fourth time that he has survived a scare. Mayers fires in a full ball, angling on middle and leg. Ali was way too early on his flick. Gets hit on the pads as he misses his shot. The Windies appeal but nothing from the umpire. Mayers convinces his captain to go for the review. It shows that the wickets were missing. West Indies lose their review!
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg for a single.
On a length and on off. Blocked out.
Another length ball, on middle. Another solid block from Ali.
Fuller ball, just around off, nips back in. Ali shoulders arms to it. The ball leaps over the off stump.
Spills it down the leg side. Ali misses his flick. The keeper does well to dive to his left and certainly saves a boundary.
Touch fuller on middle. Ali flicks it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
BEATEN! On a length and outside off. Ali looks to defend inside the line but gets beaten on the outside edge and bounces in front of the keeper. The Ultra edge shows there was an edge.
Full on middle, Defended out.
On middle, on a fuller length, tucked on the leg side for one.
Around off, on a length, pushed to mid off.
Way outside off, on a length. Left alone.
A good length ball outside off. Ali shoulders arms to it.
Very full, on off, pushed to covers to end the over.
A short ball outside off. Azam shoulders arms to it.
Lovely delivery! A short of a length, outside off. Azam looks to defend but pulls it out in the last minute.
FOUR! Good shot! Another short of a length ball on off. Azam pulls it, not quite of the middle but enough for the ball to race away to mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle, fuller length, flicked to mid-wicket.
Angles on a full length, on middle. Azam flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full on off, pushed to covers.
'NAHII YAAAAAAAAAAAR!' says Azam, which basically means 'NOOOOOOO MANNNNNN!'. Probably did not hit it as nicely as he would have liked. Short, outside off, slapped away to the man at covers.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length around off, pushed via the inner half of the blade, to mid on.
On a length, fourth stump channel, Azam looks to have a feel at this, but gets beaten.
Left alone as this was bowled outside the off pole.
On a length, outside off, Azam looks to drive but gets beaten once again.
On a shortish length, outside off, left alone.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! FIVE! Five tries it has taken for the hosts to remove Azhar Ali. That is a good catch from Holder and the Windies finally strike. On a good length this time, around off, the ball seams away as Azhar Ali hops and looks to defend. The ball catches the outside edge and goes to the left of the second slip, where Jason Holder moves that side and pouches this. It has taken some time, but Azhar Ali's lucky stay comes to an end.
Howout: c Jason Holder b Jayden Seales

Commentary: A short ball, down the leg side, Fawad Alam misses his tuck to the leg side and the keeper takes it. An appeal but nothing doing says the umpire.
Another bumper, this is bowled around off, Alam sways away from the ball.
Back of a length, nipping in, Fawad Alam hops and looks to tuck this to the leg side, but misses. Gets hit high on the pad, but it would go over the sticks this time.
Bumper on middle, ducked under by Alam.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another one bites the dust and one brings two for the hosts. This is the big, big wicket of Azam. He could have really taken the game away from them, but he does not have the desired impact in this innings. On a length, around off, nipping in, Azam looks to defend this one out, but the ball seams in and beats his inside edge, to the keeper, who takes it and appeals. The umpire just shakes his head this time. There is a discussion and they take the review, in the end. Ultra Edge rolls in now and there is a SPIKE as the ball goes past the bat, to the keeper. Cheers all around as the on-field umpire reverses his decision.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary: FOUR! Mohammad Rizwan does not need a lot of balls to get going. Gets a boundary on his very first ball. A full toss, around off, this is whipped away past mid on and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
Length on off, defended.
Short and outside off, left alone.
Around off, tucked past mid on for one.
Down the leg side, left alone.
FOUR! Short ball, around off, Mohammad Rizwan rocks on his back foot and powers this one through square leg. Classy shot.
Short, outside off, left alone.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Outside off, short in length, dabbed to point.
On a fuller length, around off, MR goes back and guides this past the point fielder. They call for the second and get it with ease.
Yorker on off, jammed out to the off side.
Length on off, defended.
Full on off, kept out again.
Around off, kept out to the off side.
Fuller in length, nice timing on this flick through mid-wicket. A couple of runs.
Full again, on off, tucked to short mid-wicket.
On a length, outside off, driven through covers and a couple are taken here.
FOUR! Timing! A short ball outside off. Rizwan gets on top of the bounce and slaps it through point for a boundary,
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Angles in a full ball, around off. Rizwan steps across and looks to push but gets beaten on the inside edge, gets hit on the pads and to the keeper. Optimistic appeal for LBW from the Windies.
Full on off, pushed to covers.

NOT OUT! A full ball, angling on middle and leg. Rizwan strides forward to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. West Indies appeal for LBW but nothing was given. They take the review and the Ultra Edge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows the impact was Umpire's call although it was hitting the wickets. So, the on-field decision stays.
On a length and on middle. Defended out.
No ball! A length ball on off. Alam blocks it out. No ball called by the umpire for overstepping.
On a length and way outside off. Left alone.
Around off, on a length. Kept out.
Full ball on middle. Alam blocks it out.
Another good length ball outside off. Alam looks to push but misses.
Another length ball outside off. Kept out.
Dot to end the over as this is on a length and outside off. Alam keeps it out.
FOUR! Good shot! A good length ball outside off. Rizwan smashes it through cover-point for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! Goes fuller now, on off. Rizwan drives it gently wide of mid off and the ball races away to the fence. Nicely played.
On a length and on off. Blocked out.
A short ball way outside off. Left alone.
Another short ball outside off. Shoukders arms to it.
Dot ball! A length ball on off. Rizwan solidly defends it to covers. Ohh wait, No Ball given for overstepping.
Way outside off delivery. Left alone.
Huge appeal but it was clearly outside off. A length ball around off. Alam looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Again gets beaten on the outside edge as Alam looks to defend.
Full on middle. Alam looks to flick but gets a soft leading edge to point.
On middle, on a length, tucked to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! This was served on a length and outside off. Alam looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On middle, flicked to square leg for a single.
On a length and way outside off. Left alone.
Comes around the wicket, a short of a length ball, on middle. Alam looks to defend but gets hit on the body.
On middle, nudged on the leg side.
A short of a length ball on middle, tucked to square leg.
Just over! A full ball outside off. Alam checks his shot and pushes it uppishly over covers for a brace.
On a length and on off, tucked on the leg side.
A length ball, lands on middle. Rizwan blocks it out.
On a length and on off. Blocked out.
Another solid block from Rizwan on the off side.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! A length ball, outside off, some inward movement. Rizwan has a poke at it but misses and gets beaten on the inside edge.
Touch fuller and outside off, defended to the off side.
Way outside off. Left alone.
A length ball outside off. Alam shoulders arms to it.
Another length ball on off. Alam pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, on a length, defended through covers for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! A simple catch to Chase and Rizwan is disappointed with himself! Holder serves a full ball, angling in, on middle. Rizwan stays back and clips it straight to square leg where Roston Chase takes a simple low catch. Another breakthrough for the Windies and Pakistan are 5 down now.
Howout: c Roston Chase b Jason Holder

Commentary: On a length on middle. Defended.
Full and outside off, driven through covers for a single. Faheem Ashraf is off the mark.
A length ball, angling down. Ashraf misses his flick.
This one lands on off and shapes away. Left alone.
Full and on off. Defended out.
Way outside off, on a length. Left alone.
Another leave by Ashraf as this is way outside off.
Full on middle. Blocked out on the leg side.
Full outside off, pushed to covers.
On a fuller length, on middle, clipped to square leg for a quick run.
A back-of-a-length delivery, around off, Ashraf looks to punch, but the ball takes the inside edge and goes past the sticks on the leg side.
Angled into the middle pole, defended out.
Serves a good length ball, on off. Kept out by Ashraf.
Brilliant delivery! Short of a length, outside off, angles away after hitting the deck, FA looks to fend at this but gets beaten.
On a length, outside off, swinging away, Alam leaves it be.
Outside off, dabbed to the off side.
Fuller ball, outside off, the ball comes back in, Alam taps this one past point for a run.
Angles a length ball, outside off, Ashraf misses his poke.

EDGED AND FOUR. Unlucky for Roach and Ashraf gets a lucky boundary. On a good length, lands outside off, seams away, Faheem Ashraf looks to drive, but the ball takes the outside edge and goes over the gully fielder, to the ropes.
Left alone as this was bowled outside off.
Floated on off, Alam prods forward and blocks.
Tossed up, around off, Alam defends.
Floated, fuller on off, Alam pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted, around off, Fawad pushes it to the off side.

FOUR BYES. There is some spin on this deck. Tossed up, outside off, the ball spins away as Alam looks to drive, but misses. The keeper and the first slip also fails to collect it. The ball goes to the ropes.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Outside off, Ashraf looks to defend inside the line but misses.
Angles a fuller ball around off, Ashraf blocks well.
Fuller, outside off, Faheem watches it go past him.
Swinging away on a length, outside off, Ashraf leaves it.
Pitches it up, outside off, Ashraf looks to drive but gets an outside edge to the gully fielder, on the bounce.
Pushed to the short cover fielder.
Flatter, outside off, pushed to covers.
Shortish again, turns away on a length outside off, Alam leaves it in the end.
Floats it up outside off, Fawad defends.
Tosses this one up and lands it on middle, Fawad Alam comes down and clips this one through mid-wicket. They get three runs this time.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Too full from Chase and Ashraf does well to get a boundary. Floated and fuller outside off, Faheem Ashraf slams this one through covers and the ball finds its way to the ropes.
Around middle, blocked out.
FOUR! Welcome to Test cricket, says Fawad Alam! Starts with a short ball, outside off, Fawad Alam goes back and crunches this one past the cover fielder for a boundary.
On off, knocked to the mid on region.
Floated, on off, knocked to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Tossed up again, on off, pushed to the leg side.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Around off and middle, Alam prods ahead and blocks. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Tossed up, full and outside off. Left alone.
Another tossed up ba, outside off. Ashraf leaves it through.
Flatter and way outside off, cuts to point.
Another flatter ball outside off. Ashraf cuts it to point again.
Full this time, outside off. Ashraf drives it through covers. The fielder chases back and does well to stop it, Two taken.
Around off, Blocked out.
Comes around the wicket, full and on middle. Alam flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Full on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Well played! A short of a length ball on middle. Ashraf stands tall and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Pure timing! Full and on off. Ashraf pushes it gently through mid off for another boundary.
LEG BYE! A length ball, angling down. Ashraf misses his flic. They take a leg bye off the pads and to fine leg.
On middle, a fuller length. Blocked out.
A loopy ball, on off, it lands and spins away. Ashraf watchfully leaves it.
Another loopy ball on off. Ashraf lets it through to the keeper.
Takes a big stride forward and defends it out.
Slightly shorter outside off, cut away to point for one.
Another short ball outside off. Alam slaps it to cover who lets it through and allows a single.
EDGY FOUR! Tossed up, outside off. Ashraf manages a thick outside edge, past the slip fielder and the ball races away to the third man fence.
On a length and on middle, pulled away wide of square leg for a couple of runs.
Full on off, Defended out.
NO BALL! A pacy short ball, on the bodyline. Alam awkwardly defends it to covers. No ball called as Jayden Seales has overstepped.
Around off, kept out.
Angles in a length ball, on middle and leg. Alam looks to flick but misses it.
Length ball, on off. Alam defends it to the off side.
Another solid defense from Alam to end the over.
Tossed up, outside off. Left alone to the keeper.
Full on middle. Ashraf strides and blocks it out.
Full again, outside off. Ashraf shoulders arms to it.
Flatter ball on middle. Ashraf punches it off the back foot to the bowler.
Full, on off. Ashraf pushes it through covers for a single.
Shorter and on middle. Alam blocks it out watchfully.
On a length and outside off, punched to covers.
Serves a full ball on middle. Ashraf flicks it to deep square leg for one.
Full again on middle, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Alam got something on it. A short ball, angling on middle. Alam pulls it over the keeper's head for a boundary. 150 up for Pakistan.
Another short ball on middle. Alam sits under it.
Three taken in the end! A full ball on middle. Alam flicks it through mid-wicket. The square leg fielder comes across and cuts it off. A partnership of fifty between these two.
FOUR! Gets the gap and the boundary. Tossed up, fuller outside off, Alam drills this one past the cover fielder and the ball wins the race to the ropes.
Darted on the pads, Alam tickles this one to the fine leg region for a couple.
Around off, defended out.
Tossed up, around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Darted on off, Alam keeps it out.
Outside off, dabbed to backward point.
On a length, around off, kept out nicely.
Length ball, outside off, swinging away, left alone.
Length outside off, left alone.
Fuller on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Similar line and length as the last ball, Ashraf pushes this to the right of mid off.

FOUR! Beats the fielder this time. Ashraf moves to 30 now. On a good length, around the off pole, Faheem Ashraf shows the full face of the blade and pushes this one past the mid on fielder, for a boundary.
FOUR! The boundaries are coming along nicely now. Floats this one up, on the pads, Fawad Alam tickles this one to the fine leg fence.
Flicked through square leg for one.
Given air, outside off, pushed through point for one.
Around off and middle, nudged to the leg side for a run.
Tossed up, at the base of off, Faheem defends.
Serves a full toss, outside off, pushed back to Roston.
Around off, on a length, Alam looks to work this to the leg side, but the ball takes the edge and goes towards point.
Length around off, nudged to the leg side.
Length outside off, Alam defends inside the line and gets beaten.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Outside off, on a length, Alam looks to leave, but lets his bat hang. Takes the lower half of the blade and goes through gully, for one.
FOUR! Faheem Ashraf gets a boundary. On a length, on the pads, whipped away to deep square leg for a boundary.
On the pads, nudged to the leg side for a run.
On middle, pushed to point for one.
Darted on middle, defended out.
On off and middle, pushed to mid on. Alam wanted one, but then denies it himself.
Gives it air this time, on the pad, Fawad tickles this to square leg for a single.
Around off, tucked through mid-wicket for one.
A good length ball outside off. Ashraf watchfully lets it through.
Nicely played but just for two! A full ball outside off. Ashraf creams his drive through covers before the fielder chases it back. Two taken.
On middle. Ashraf looks to defend but gets an inside edge to the leg side for a single.
Full on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Fuller ball outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller again outside off. Left alone.
Lovely delivery! A good length ball, around off. Ashraf looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge.
On a length and way outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball on off, driven to mid off.
A good length ball, just around off. Ashraf watchfully leaves it to the keeper.
FOUR! Smashed! A full ball, on off. Ashraf gets low and smashes it wide of mid off for a boundary.
Around off, kept out.

OUT! RUN OUT! Much needed breakthrough for West Indies and this stand has finally been broken! Faheem Ashraf has to walk back disappointed as he would feel that he gave away his wicket here. A short-of-a-length ball on middle. Alam hops and tucks it to square leg for a quick single. Chase there grabs and scores a direct hit at the striker's end. He and his peers are confident about it. The TV umpire had a quick look and Ashraf is a goner. He walks back for 44.
Howout: run out (Roston Chase)

Commentary: On a length and on off. Defended out.
A length ball, angling down. Shah looks to flick but misses.
Appeal for LBW but not given! Angles in a length ball on middle and leg. Shah misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Around off, on a length, pushed to covers.
Spills it way down the leg side. Shah misses his pull. The keeper does well to grab it on his left side.
A full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Angles in a full ball, on the pads. Alam misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
On a length on middle. Defended.
FOUR! Good shot! A full ball on off. Alam pushes it gently, wide of mid on for a boundary. A welcome boundary.
Length ball way outside off. Alam chases a wayward delivery and misses it.
On a length and outside off. Kept out.
Fuller ball on off, pushed to mid on.
On a length, outside off. Shah defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Brilliant catch by Joshua Da Silva! Kyle Mayers gets his first wicket as well! A good length ball outside off. Yasir Shah hangs his bat out and looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge, to the keeper, where Joshua Da Silva dives to his right and takes a wonderful catch. Yasir Shah goes for a duck.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kyle Mayers

Commentary: Full ball, swinging in, on middle. Ali flicks it to square leg for a single.

FOUR! Not the way he wanted to reach his fifty but he will take it! A full ball outside off. Alam looks to push but gets a thick outside edge, past the slip cordon for a boundary. A hard-fought innings from him and he have to bat further now and make sure Pakistan reach a decent score.
A length ball on off. Alam watchfully defends it.
Length outside off, left alone.
Length ball outside off again, Ali pokes at this but misses.
Outside off, short in length, dabbed to the left of backward point.
Fuller ball, outside off, Ali swings wildly at this but misses.
Angles a length ball, on middle, nudged to the leg side.
Fuller-ball, on middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Down the leg side, Alam looks to flick but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
A carbon copy of the previous ball.
Good length delivery, around off and middle, Alam goes back and whips this past the square leg fielder. By the time fine leg can run around and collect the ball, two runs were taken.
Way outside off, left alone.
Pushed to the left of mid on for a run. 200 up for Pakistan!
Angling away from around off, Alam chops this, on the bounce, to the slip cordon.
Yorker on off, Alam pushes it back to the bowler.
Bangs in a short one on the body, pulled to fine leg for one.
On the body, flicked to the leg side for one.
A fumble and a run. Around off, pulled to the left of square leg, who moves that side and only half-stops the ball, for one.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ali lofts this one over point and comes back for the second run.
Outside off, Alam makes a leave.
Fuller-ball, outside off, Fawad leaves it again.
Sticks with the full ball, around off, this is nudged to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Bumper on off, Alam ducks under this.
Slants this one down the leg side, Alam looks to tuck but misses.
Full on off, worked to the leg side.
EDGED AND FOUR! Fuller, outside off, Hasan Ali swings wildly at this, but the ball only takes the outside edge and goes over the slip cordon, for a boundary, to third man.
FOUR LEG BYES. More vital runs for Pakistan. A length ball, strays way too much on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses and the ball takes the pad and runs away to the fine leg fence.

FOUR! 12 runs off the last 3 balls! Ali is being very positive here. On a good length, around off, Hasan Ali lofts this one over the mid on fielder and the ball takes a couple of bounces and goes past the ropes.
Bouncer outside off, Hasan sits under this one.
Short of a length, around off, Hasan looks to block but gets beaten here.

OUT! CAUGHT! The fielder there was strategically placed there and Seales strikes. Hasan Ali was looking to attack and keep the scoreboard ticking, but he holes out here. On a shortish length, angling on the body, Hasan Ali looks to hook this one away, but the ball takes the glove and lobs towards short fine leg, where Kyle Mayers takes the catch.
Howout: c Kyle Mayers b Jayden Seales

Commentary: A fuller ball outside off. Alam pushes it to covers.

OUT! TIMBER! That is a huge wicket of Alam. In space of three balls, 2 wickets for the Windies. A full ball, slanting across, just outside off. Alam gets tempted and goes for an expensive drive but ends up getting an inside edge, hitting the stumps.
Howout: b Jason Holder

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Two-in-two for Holder! That's the end of the Pakistani inning as they end on 217. A good length ball, shaping away, around off. Abbas hangs his bat out and looks to defend but gets the smallest of nicks of his outside edge to the keeper who dives forward and takes a lovely catch.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jason Holder

Commentary: Starts with a good length ball on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite tucks it on the leg side.
Goes fuller now, on middle. Brathwaite blocks it out.
A short of a length ball, outside off, little bit of away shape. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend but misses it.
On a length and outside off. Left alone to the keeper.
Around off, on a length. Braithwaite blocks it on the off side.
Maiden over to begin for Pakistan! On a length and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite solidly blocks it.
Starts with a wayward delivery, down the leg side. Powell misses his flick.
Another length delivery, down the leg side. Powell misses his flick again.
On a length and way outside off. Left alone.
BYE! West Indies are underway! Spills it down the leg side. The keeper fumbles to carry it and parries it to fine leg for a bye.
On a length and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it through.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! A length ball, slanting across, outside off. Powell looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! TAKEN! Powell was beaten on the previous delivery but this time, he manages to kiss the outside edge! A good length ball, angling on middle. Powell looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge, towards the second slip. Imran Butt there dives forward and to his right to take a brilliant low catch. The Pakistani players were celebrating but the umpires wanted to check for a fair catch. The replay shows that it is a fair catch and Pakistan gets the first blood as Powell walks back for a duck.
Howout: c Imran Butt b Mohammad Abbas

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Dream start from Mohammad Abbas! A good length ball, angling on middle and leg. Bonner looks to defend but was too late on his shot, gets hit on the pads. The Pakistani players appeal and the finger goes up straightaway. Bonner takes the review immediately. Ultra Edge confirms no bat. Ball Tracking shows Umpire's call on the wickets and the on-field decision stays. Nkrumah Bonner goes back on a golden duck. Mohammad Abbas is on a Hat-Trick.
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Abbas

Commentary: Easily negotiated! On a length and outside off. Chase shoulders arms to it.
Full ball on middle. Chase tucks it to mid-wicket who does well to stop it.
On a length, on middle. Defended. Excellent over from Mohammad Abbas.
There is turn! A tossed up ball, outside off, it lands and spins away. Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to the first slip who catches it on a bounce.
Flatter ball on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Kraigg Brathwaite is off the mark! Full on middle, tucked to mid on for a quick single.
Floated, outside off. Chase leaves it through.
This time prods forward and defends it on the off side.
Very full on middle. Blocked out.
BEATEN! Lovely start from Mohammad Abbas! Good length ball around off, Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge.
Full ball on the pads, Brathwaite clips it to deep square leg for two.
Good length ball on off, Brathwaite defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Brathwaite makes a leave to the keeper.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery! Good length ball around off, Brathwaite looks to defend but misses.
Full ball on off, Kraigg defends it to cover.
FOUR LEG BYES! Good length ball on the pads, Chase looks to flick but it goes off the pads to fine leg for four leg byes.
FOUR LEG BYES! On a length ball on the pads, Chase misses his flick and it goes off the pads to fine leg for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Chase flicks it to mid-wicket.

Full on middle, Chase pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! Beautifully played by Chase! Full on middle, Chase clips it through mid on for a boundary.
On off, kept out.

Full down the leg side, Kraigg looks to flick but misses.
Full on middle, Brathwaie works it to mid on.
FOUR! Creamed! Full on off, Brathwaite leans and drives it through mid off for a boundary.

A length ball way outside off. Brathwaite leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a length and way outside off. Left alone.
Angles this one on a length, on middle. Brathwaite blocks it on the leg side.
A good length ball on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it through square leg for a single.
FOUR! EDGY RUNS! A good length ball outside off. Chase hangs his bat out and gets toe end of his bat, past the diving keeper to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full and way outside off. Chase leaves it alone to the keeper.
A full ball outside off. Kraigg shoulders arms to it.
A length ball outside off. Left alone.

On middle, on a length, pushed to mid on.
A length ball, outside off. Defended.
Another length ball on middle. Chase solidly blocks it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Hasan Ali prevails and there comes his iconic celebration. Tell you what, there was no need for Roston Chase to go after it. A full ball, around off, shaping away from the batter. Chase gets tempted and goes for an expensive drive but manages a thick outside edge, to the keeper. Rizwan moves to his right and pouches it wonderfully.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Hasan Ali

BYE! Spills it down the leg side, Blackwood misses his flick. The keeper fumbles and they take a run.
Full on middle, Defended.
A good length ball outside off. Jermaine shoulders arms to it.
Appeal for LBW but not given! A length ball, angling down. Jermaine Blackwood looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the pads. Was missing the leg stump.
Way outside off. Left alone.

On a length, on middle. Blackwood misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.

That just dropped short of the keeper! A good length ball, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend but gets am outside edge to the keeper. Mohammad Rizwan behind, dives forward but grabs it on a bounce.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
Full on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a brace.

On middle, on a length. Blackwood gets an inside edge on the pads.

Full ball on off, Blackwood defends it to cover. LUNCH ON DAY 2!

SWING AND A MISS! Good length ball outside off, Blackwood looks to swing it away but misses.
Full on middle, mistimed to mid on.

Shortish ball on middle, Blackwood hops and defends it back to the bowler.

Full on middle, KB defends it out.

Three now! Full ball outside off, Blackwood drives it through cover for three. 100 comes up for West Indies.
Good length ball on middle, Kraigg defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, defended to cover.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jermaine Blackwood has thrown it away! A poor shot in the circumstances and a good partnership has been broken. Full on off, Blackwood looks to go over mid on but the bat turns in his hand and ends up mistiming it to mid on where Mohammad Abbas takes the catch.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! Double strike from Shaheen Afridi and Kyle Mayers goes for a duck! Shaheen will be on a Hat-Trick. Good length ball on off, Mayers looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Shaheen Afridi appeals and up goes the finger. Mayers has a chat with his partner and decides not to take the review.
Howout: lbw b Shaheen Afridi

THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!

OUT! TAKEN! First ball of the new spell and Seales strikes this time. Abid Ali does not last for long here and he walks back. Not what Pakistan wanted here. Jayden Seales serves a short ball, outside the off pole. The ball hits the deck and shoots up this time. Abid Ali goes back and looks to cut this one away, but gets done by the bounce. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards Jason Holder at second slip, who moves to his left and pouches this. Pakistan leads by 29 runs!
Howout: c Jason Holder b Jayden Seales

Angling on a length outside off, Alam leaves it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Brilliant, brilliant bowling from Seales and he gets his second wicket of the over. Perfect line, perfect length, and it is a perfect ball to get rid of Alam. He goes back for a 3-ball duck this time. On a length, around off, the ball hits the deck and straightens this time. Fawad Alam has a poke at this, but misses, as the ball takes the outside edge, and goes to the keeper, where Joshua Da Silva takes a good catch.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

FOUR! Welcome boundary! Serves a full ball outside off. Roach opens his bat face and squeezes it through the slip cordon for a boundary.
On the pads, this is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Just away of the gully fielder! A short of a length ball outside off. Roach dabs it through the gully region for two.
Full on middle, pushed wide of mid on for a single.
On middle, tucked on the leg side for a single.
BYE! Misses everyone! A good length ball outside off. Roach looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. It bounces in front of the keeper who parries it to the off side for a single.
Angles it on the pads. Joshua Da Silva misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
A length ball on middle, pulled away to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A full ball, on off. Joshua Da Silva drives it off the inner half to the leg side for a single.
On middle, clipped to fine leg for one more.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Pakistan are two wickets away from a win! A good length ball outside off. Joshua Da Silva looks to defend away from his body but manages to kiss his outside edge to the keeper who takes a brilliant low catch. Joshua Da Silva walks back disappointed as he knows he gave away his wicket here. Pakistani players are celebrating as they know, they are not far away.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Very full on middle. Warrican tucks it on the leg side.
Appeal for LBW not given! A length ball, angling on the pads. Jomel Warrican misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
On middle. Blocked out.
A short of a length ball outside off. Roach goes for the pull but fails to connect it.
A good length ball outside off. Roach looks to defend but gets an outside edge to the keeper who collects it on a bounce.
A short of a length ball, on the body, clipped to mid-wicket for one.
A short of a length ball outside off. Jomel Warrican hops and taps it wide of point and collects two.
FOUR! EDGY RUNS! Just 19 required now for the Windies! A  full ball, outside off. Jomel Warrican gets a thick outside edge as he looks to defend through the slip cordon for a boundary.

DROPPED! Has Hasan Ali dropped the match? A short of a length ball, outside off. Kemar Roach pulls it, does not gets the distance. Hits it towards deep mid-wicket where Hasan Ali runs across but does not hold it out.  A single taken.
Around off. Blocked out.
A short ball on middle. Jomel Warrican half ducks but keeps his bat out, gets some gloves on it to the leg side.
This time he blocks it out solidly. On a length, on middle.
Way outside off delivery. Left alone.
LEG BYE! On the pads. Warrican misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. They take a leg bye as it rolls to fine leg. 17 runs needed now.
On a length, outside off. Warrican looks to defend but misses.
On middle. Blocked out.
Outside off. Left alone.

OUT! CAUGHT BY Mohammad Rizwan! Brilliant, Absolutely brilliant from Rizwan! Pakistan are now one wicket away to win it! A pacy short ball on middle.  Jomel Warrican goes for the pull but manages a leading edge, in the air and towards deep fine leg. There were four fielders converging for the catch with the keeper as well. He ran all the ground, kept his eyes on it and dives a full stretch forward to take a spectacular catch.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Hasan Ali

Commentary: A good length ball, on middle. Roach pushes it through covers for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Seales watchfully leaves it. 16 needed to win.
A full ball, on middle, this is flicked to the fine leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Seals solidly blocks it. No ball given for overstepping.
A full ball, angling on middle. Blocked out.
Spills it way down the leg side. Seales misses his flick.
Way outside off. Left alone.
On a length, around off. Seales looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge to the first slip, on a bounce.
On middle. Solidly blocked out.
Full ball, on middle, this is flicked in front of square leg for two.
Around off. Roach blocks it out.
A full ball, on off. Roach pushes it to long off for a single.
10 runs needed now! A full ball, on middle. Seales nudges it on the leg side and takes a single.
A short ball on middle. Roach mistimes his pull to point. The ball was in the air for a while but away from the fielder.
A length ball way outside off. Left alone. 9 runs needed now.
LEG BYE. A full ball, angling on the pads. Roach misses his heave and gets hit on the pads. They take a leg bye as it rolls on the leg side.
Huge appeal for LBW but not given! A good length ball, angling on middle. Seales gets his bat down in time. Pakistan optimistically appeal for it.
A full ball, on middle. Seales flicks it to deep square leg and takes a single.
A good length ball, outside off. Roach gets a thick outside edge as he looks to defend to the first slip on a bounce, he parries it to third man for a single.
A full ball, outside off. Seales shoulders arms to it.
6 runs needed now! A pacy short ball on off. Seales lets it through to the keeper who leaps up to collect it.
On a length, on middle, tucked on the leg side. They decide against the single.

FOUR! EDGY RUNS! Just two runs needed now! A full ball, outside off. Kemar Roach prods to defend but gets a thick outside edge to the right of the keeper who dives but it bounces just in front of him and the ball races away to the fence.
A length ball, on off. Roach defends it to mid on.
A length ball, on off. Roach defends it out solidly.

Here comes the winning runs. Kemar Roach has completed the job for his team. A full-length ball, outside off. Roach punches it through cover. The batters take two comfortably. This is a remarkable win for the hosts. WEST INDIES WIN BY 1 wicket. What a Test game did we just witness here!
